## Conventions & Patterns

### Multi-Tenancy
- Every table has `tenant_id text not null references tenants(id) on delete cascade`
- Composite primary keys: `(tenant_id, <entity_id>)`
- RLS policies use `current_setting('app.tenant_id', true)`
- `tenant_conn(x_tenant_id)` async context manager sets GUC and returns connection
- All API endpoints require `X-Tenant-ID` header

### Database
- Raw asyncpg queries (no ORM); parameterized with `$1, $2, ...`
- Migrations numbered `0001` through `0016` (sequential)
- JSONB columns use `_json` suffix (e.g., `target_json`, `bindings_json`)
- JSON serialized via `json.dumps()` before INSERT, cast with `$N::jsonb`
- Multi-step mutations wrapped in `async with conn.transaction()`
- Append-only tables (audit_log, excel_sync_events) have SELECT+INSERT RLS only

### API Design
- All routers registered under `/api/v1` prefix in `main.py`
- Pydantic `BaseModel` for request bodies
- FastAPI `Header()` for tenant/user context
- `Query(alias="format")` pattern to avoid Python keyword conflicts
- Error responses: `HTTPException(status_code, detail_string)`
- `FinModelError` hierarchy with custom exception handler

### Services
- `ArtifactStore` for file-based persistence (save/load by tenant/type/id)
- `BillingService` as shared singleton via `deps.py`
- LLM router with dual-path billing and usage recording
- Integration framework with abstract base + concrete adapters (Xero)
- OAuth tokens encrypted at rest via Fernet

### Frontend (Next.js)
- App Router with `app/` directory structure
- TypeScript strict mode (Vercel build enforces type checking)
- Supabase auth with middleware-based session handling
- API calls via `lib/api.ts` helper functions

### Testing
- `pytest-asyncio` with `asyncio_mode = "auto"`
- Coverage: `--cov=apps --cov=shared`
- Golden tests compare against known-good manufacturing outputs
- Unit tests mock DB connections and external services

## Implementation Phases (Completed)

### Phase 1 (VA-P1): Core Platform
Baselines, changesets, runs, engine, KPIs, statements, DB migrations 0001-0008, RLS, health, metrics, notifications, connection pool, indexes.

### Phase 2 (VA-P2): Draft Workspace & Jobs
Celery job queue, draft session CRUD with state machine, async MC simulation, LLM governance/guardrails, venture wizard, notifications UI, DLQ pattern.

### Phase 3 (VA-P3): Analysis & Scenarios
Distribution engine, Monte Carlo runner with seeded RNG, DCF valuation (annualized trailing 12-month FCF), multiples valuation, sensitivity analysis, scenario CRUD with batch compare (`ANY($2::text[])`).

### Phase 4 (VA-P4): Enterprise Features
OAuth2 integrations (Xero adapter, HMAC-signed state, Fernet encryption), Stripe billing (subscriptions, usage metering, webhooks), audit log (19 event types, CSV/JSON export, checksums), covenant monitoring (multi-period breach detection), GDPR compliance (export + anonymization), CSV import with column mapping.

### Phase 5 (VA-P5): Excel & Memos
Excel live links (connections CRUD, pull/push with binding resolution), Excel export (.xlsx with IS/BS/CF/KPI sheets), memo packs (IC memo, credit memo, valuation note with XSS-safe HTML generation), Office.js add-in scaffold.

## Remaining Phases (Not Started)
- **Phase 6 (VA-P6)**: Workflow & Approvals
- **Phase 7 (VA-P7)**: Budgeting & Board Packs (VA-P7-01 through VA-P7-12)

